{"questionId":"26595","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graphs of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math> intersect at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, as shown in&nbsp;the following diagrams.</p>\n<p>In <strong>diagram 1</strong>, the region enclosed by the lines <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis has&nbsp;been shaded.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/84e37c6b34bfe1a18448581ac69b6cc57a28510c.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In <strong>diagram 2</strong>, the region enclosed by the curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, and the lines <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis has been shaded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3ce2de8dcf5764bcc809840b29475302e9ab6380.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down an integral for the area of the shaded region in<strong> diagram 2</strong>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for the limits <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> in correct location. Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for an integral of the quadratic function, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math> must be included. Do not accept “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>” in place of the function, given that two equations are in the question.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26595","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ2.6b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down an integral for the area of the shaded region in diagram 2.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}